OL,3,CGreen Party claim victory in by-
OL,4,Celection unseating Labour stronghold
OL,6,FThe defeat is a major blow for Sir
OL,7,FKeir Starmer's leadership and is
OL,8,Flikely to add pressure on calls for
OL,9,Fhis resignation.
OL,11,FA Green Party said: "Things are
OL,12,Ffeeling positive. Not wanting to get
OL,13,Fahead of ourselves, but everything
OL,14,Fthat we thought that was going to be
OL,15,Fhappening looks like it's happening.
OL,17,F"Whatever happens, I think it's fair
OL,18,Fto say that Greens are here to stay
OL,19,Fnow as a progressive voice in British
OL,20,Fpolitics.
OL,26,@sD@UOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1772193822
OL,3,CGreen Party claim victory in by-
OL,4,Celection unseating Labour stronghold
OL,6,F"We've said from the start we're not
OL,7,Fhere to be disappointed by Labour, but
OL,8,Fwe're here to replace them.
OL,10,F"And from day one of the by-election,
OL,11,Fwe've said that Greens are the only
OL,12,Fparty that could beat Reform. And I
OL,13,Fthink tonight we're seeing both of
OL,14,Fthose things potentially coming true.
OL,16,F"I think it's a seismic moment in
OL,17,FBritish politics where Greens are
OL,18,Fshowing that they're a party that can
OL,19,Fprotect the country from the threat of
OL,20,FReform, and that Labour's not up to
OL,21,Fthe job."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUxD@AOU}D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
