FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1772193822
OL,3,CGreen Party claim victory in by-
OL,4,Celection unseating Labour stronghold
OL,6,FGwynne, who had been an MP since 2005,
OL,7,Fwon the most recent July 2024 general
OL,8,Felection with a majority of more than
OL,9,F13,000, having received 50.8% of the
OL,10,Fvote.
OL,12,FMany within the Labour Party had hoped
OL,13,Fhis resignation would pave the way for
OL,14,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham
OL,15,Fto return to the House of Commons, but
OL,16,Fthe move was blocked by the party's
OL,17,FNational Executive Committee.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1772193822
OL,3,CGreen Party claim victory in by-
OL,4,Celection unseating Labour stronghold
OL,6,FIn a statement, the Labour Party said
OL,7,Fthe NEC had decided to deny Mr Burnham
OL,8,Fpermission to stand in order to avoid
OL,9,F"an unnecessary election for the
OL,10,Fposition of Greater Manchester mayor".
OL,12,FThe party said a mayoral by-election
OL,13,F"would have a substantial and
OL,14,Fdisproportionate impact on party
OL,15,Fcampaign resources" before local and
OL,16,Fdevolved elections in May.
OL,18,FThe Greens' victory at Gorton and
OL,19,FDenton represents the sixth largest
OL,20,FLabour majority to be overturned at a
OL,21,Fby-election since the Second World War.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
